  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6594.35 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-23B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+20B), dealers are currently in buy mode as they're short gamma below current levels. The BREAKOUT regime with -48B total GEX means dealers will amplify any directional moves - they'll aggressively buy weakness toward 6590/6580 and sell strength into 6605. Watch for explosive moves if we break below the 6590-6580 negative gamma cluster or rejection/chop if we push into the 6605 positive gamma wall.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect violent swings with dealers fueling moves away from the tight 6590-6605 range.",
